\par }{\b\f5 Program Startup
\par }{\f5 
You must start Windows before running Kermit.  Once Windows is running, you can start Kermit by double-clicking on its icon in the Program Manager (if you installed one) or by double-clicking on KERMIT.EXE in the Windows File Manager.  If you are using Wi
ndows 95, you may start Kermit through the Start button on the task bar.
\par 
\par Kermit follows all Windows standards.  Those familiar with other MS Windows applications should be able to use Kermit without trouble.
