\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\tqdec\tx9360 {\f5 To recall a session you saved previously, choose Open... from the File Menu.  The standard Windows Open dialog will be displaye
d to allow you to choose the session save file to be opened.
\par 
\par By default, the Open dialog will display all files with an extension of ".KRM" in the directory that the Kermit program is stored in.
\par 
\par After choosing a session file to load, Kermit will check to see if the previous session had a connection active.  If so, you will be asked to confirm that you want to disconnect.  If you choose not to disconnect, you will be returned to the previous sessi
on with the connection still active.
\par 
\par If the session you have chosen to load has the Auto Connect on Open option set in the Session Settings dialog, Kermit will attempt to establish a connection with the remote system immediately.
\par 
\par It is also possible to Open a saved session at the time you invoke the Kermit program.  You may specify the name of a session save file on the command line that is used to invoke Kermit.  The specified session file will be automatically loaded instead of 
the default settings that would normally be loaded.
\par 
\par If you hav
e set up Kermit as an Icon in the Program Manager, the command line is one of the entries in the Properties dialog for the Icon.  This feature makes it possible to create several Icons in the Program Manager for Kermit and each one could start Kermit with
