\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\tqdec\tx9360 {\i\f5 Connection
\par }{\f5 Type of connection desired.  Dial and answer apply to modems.  If no modem is in use, you should choose direct.  If dial is chosen, a phone number to dial should be supplied.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Dial Init\tab 
\par }{\f5 The sequence of characters that should be send to the modem to initialize it for dial-out usage..  The default is usually OK.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Dial Cmd
\par }{\f5 The sequence of characters that should be sent to the modem to cause it to dial a phone number.  The default is usually OK.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Answer Init
\par }{\f5 The sequence of characters that should be send to the modem to initialize it for answer usage.  The default is usually OK.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Hangup\tab 
\par }{\f5 The sequence of characters that should be send to the modem to cause it to hang up the phone line.  The default is usually OK.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Escape\tab 
\par }{\f5 The sequence of characters that should be send to the modem while online prior to sending command strings.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Connect
\par }{\f5 The message that the modem will send when a connection has been successfully established.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Redial
\par }{\f5 Number of times to redial a number that fails to connect followed by the number of seconds to wait between attempts.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Wait
\par }{\f5 Number of seconds to wait from the time a number is dialed to get a successful connection message.
