\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\tqdec\tx9360 {\i\f5 Font
\par }{\f5 Select from the list of available fonts.  Only "fixed-pitch" fonts will be displayed.  If a font called "Terminal" is available, it is recommended because it is specifically designed to work with communication programs.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Size
\par }{\f5 Point size for font.  A larger point size means a larger font displayed on the window.
\par 
\par }{\i\f5 Sample\tab 
\par }{\f5 A sample display of the currently selected font.
\par 
\par }{\b\f5 Note}{\f5 :  After changing the selected font, Kermit will attempt to resize the terminal window to provide a full 80 by 25 display.  If the window can not be expanded enough to do this, scroll bars will be displayed.
\par 
\par When a new session is created, Kermit requests a default fixed-pitch font from Windows.  In some cases (depending on your display driver and resolution), windows does a poor job of selecting a default font.
